      "author": "st-vin",
      "description": "## Release notes \r\n\r\n### Summary\r\nThis release incorporates feedback from the Obsidian maintainers to better align with current plugin guidelines and best practices.\r\n\r\n### Changes\r\n- **Path handling**: Normalized user-provided folder/file paths using `normalizePath` to avoid platform-specific path issues.\r\n- **Vault API adoption**: Replaced several direct `adapter.*` file operations with the **Vault API** for better compatibility and recommended usage.\r\n- **Safer file updates**: Switched vocabulary updates to use `Vault.append` (instead of read-modify-write).\r\n- **Event lifecycle**: Registered the flashcard interval using `registerInterval` so it is automatically cleaned up when the plugin is disabled (no manual `clearInterval` needed).\r\n- **Ribbon toggle removed**: Removed the plugin’s “show ribbon icon” toggle setting (Obsidian v1.1+ lets users manage ribbon items directly).\r\n- **Improved folder setting UX**: Added type-ahead folder selection for the vocabulary folder path using `AbstractInputSuggest`.\r\n- **Settings clarity**: Flashcard interval setting is now only shown when flashcard popups are enabled.\r\n- **Disclosure**: Updated README to disclose that the plugin downloads the large dictionary JSON file on first initialization (and caches it locally).\r\n\r\n### Notes / Migration\r\n- If you previously disabled the ribbon icon via the plugin setting, that toggle no longer exists. Use Obsidian’s built-in ribbon customization instead.\r\n- The dictionary file download still occurs only if the cached file is missing; an internet connection is required for the initial download.\r\n\r\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/st-vin/obsidian-lexicon-dictionary-plugin/compare/1.0.3...1.0.4",
